    "d41ffe8e-9091-4d6e-a127-34795478b5d1": {
      "type": "simple",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "You invoke the power of the Void, summoning swirling bands of inky energy to bind your foes. Choose up to three creatures you can see within 60 feet that are each within 20 feet of another chosen target. Each target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or be magically restrained by void energies and take 3d6 psychic damage. On a successful save, a target takes half damage and isn’t restrained, and it can’t be affected again by this casting of ",
              "textFormat": "paragraph"
            },
            {
              "text": "{{Void_Shackle}}",
              "variable": true,
              "textFormat": "paragraph"
            },
            {
              "text": ".\n\nA restrained target can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success. The void bands are insubstantial: any creature that moves out of the spell’s area or breaks free of restraints is no longer restrained but still suffers no further damage from this casting.",
              "textFormat": "paragraph"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "parentId": "1e2530e8-fa9d-4a10-a92c-044ac2d34211",
      "styles": {
        "paddingBottom": "8px"
      },
      "id": "d41ffe8e-9091-4d6e-a127-34795478b5d1"
    },
    "130b927a-c63e-4a38-8649-30d1882d87a7": {
      "type": "simple",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Lore",
              "textFormat": "underline-h2"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "parentId": "1e2530e8-fa9d-4a10-a92c-044ac2d34211",
      "id": "130b927a-c63e-4a38-8649-30d1882d87a7"
    },
    "f75326da-79c7-4663-8034-32565457ef95": {
      "type": "simple",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Practitioners of the Mantis Clan’s void schools originated ",
              "textFormat": "paragraph"
            },
            {
              "text": "{{Void_Shackle}}",
              "variable": true,
              "textFormat": "paragraph"
            },
            {
              "text": ", believing the nothingness between the worlds could be shaped into imprisonment. Many imperial Shugenja argue its use risks summoning actual void spirits, yet the spell endures among those who see the Void as the source of true freedom—freedom from flesh, thought, and life itself.",
              "textFormat": "paragraph"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "parentId": "1e2530e8-fa9d-4a10-a92c-044ac2d34211",
      "styles": {
        "paddingBottom": "8px"
      },
      "id": "f75326da-79c7-4663-8034-32565457ef95"
    },
